President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Minnesota and authorized federal assistance to support recovery efforts from severe storms, winds, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred from May 8 to May 13, 2022. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The designated counties for assistance include Aitkin, Big Stone, Cass, Chippewa, Cottonwood, Douglas, Grant, Kandiyohi, Lac qui Parle, Lincoln, Morrison, Nobles, Pope, Redwood, Renville, Stearns, Stevens, Swift, Todd, Traverse, Wadena, Wilkin, and Yellow Medicine. Brian F. Schiller has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.